<p>A folder or a file can be set to the SVN ignore list as follows:</p>  <pre><code>$ cd /path/to/folder/for/example/to/project/root $ svn propset svn:ignore ./folder . </code></pre>  <p>Check:</p>  <pre><code>$ svn proplist -v Properties on '.':   svn:ignore     ./folder </code></pre>  <p>Then the folder is ignored on commits and doesn't get displayed in the TortoiseSVN commit dialog list.</p>  <p>It also should work for any path / subfolder:</p>  <pre><code>$ cd /path/to/folder/for/example/to/project/root/subfolder $ ssvn propset svn:ignore ./sub/folder . </code></pre>  <p>And it works for SVN:</p>  <pre><code>$ svn proplist -v Properties on '.':   svn:ignore     ./sub/folder </code></pre>  <p>But despite the properties ignored folders are shown in the TortoiseSVN commit files/folders list. It works, when I change the properties of the <code>/sub/folder</code>. But I'd like to have a global / project wide "ignore list" with all the SVN ignore list features (paths, subfolders, wildcards, etc.).</p>  <p><strong>How to disable ignored subfolders in the TortoiseSVN commit window?</strong></p>